Subject: Re: [VB] switched to dual carbs = lower mpg

----- Original Message ----- 

> I recently put a set of Solex 35mm dual carbs on my 1600 motor.  I like
> the results (more power, better power curve) but I seem to have lost
> mpg.  I was running 20-24 for my single 34-pict, now I am down to 16-19.
> Is this normal? & how do I tune things for better mpg's? These carbs
> only appear to have an idle jet mixture screw.  I don't know what size
> main jets they come with but do I need to swap jets or something?


Yes, dual carbs are capable of better mileage than a single carb.

But you have to spend time jetting them correctly to get them dialed in
right. No carburetor is going to be jetted "right" right out of the box.

Eric Allred
